RAPPER Sjava hates lingerie, but prefers a petticoat. On Valentines Day, he told fans on social media he doesn’t like this underwear and doesn’t understand why women wear it. “Ayikho into engiyizonda njenge lanjare,” he said (I hate lingerie with a passion). His post attracted different opinions. Some asked if he prefers tights instead of a lingerie. But he responded: “Why are you even putting on clothes when going to bed?” Deliwe asked: “So you prefer a petticoat?” to which he responded: “now you’re talking.” ALSO READ |KULI ROBERTS WILL BE LAID TO REST THIS WEEK In his interactions with his fans he claimed lingerie made him very angry. Sbonelo asked: “So it makes you angry?” to which he responded: “Very angry.” He also made it clear that no amount of convincing was going to change his mind. Tweep Mthomde argued: “But it makes women sexy.” But the rapper was still not convinced, asking: “Sexy where?”